HEADWORD: Chrysene
<hw>Chry"sene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>chryso`s</grk> gold.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>One of the
higher aromatic hydrocarbons of coal tar, allied to naphthalene and
anthracene. It is a white crystalline substance,
<chform>C18H12</chform>, of strong blue fluorescence, but generally
colored yellow by impurities.</def><-- ##err in orig, "naphthalene" was
misspelled "napthalene". -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

